= Findings and Discussion

== Introduction

This chapter presents and interprets the empirical results generated by the multimodal M&A synergy prediction pipeline. Every quantitative claim made below is derived from the cross-validated experimental results stored in the project's results directory and rendered in real time by the _Deal Intelligence Terminal_ — a purpose-built interactive Streamlit dashboard that serves as the operational proof-of-concept for this research. Where appropriate, the chapter explicitly references the named visualisation panels within the terminal to bridge the gap between static academic text and interactive empirical evidence. Examiners wishing to interrogate any claim dynamically are directed to the dashboard.

The chapter proceeds as follows. Section 4.2 reports the full model ablation ladder. Section 4.3 weaponises the M2 reversal as a first-class theoretical finding. Sections 4.4 through 4.6 resolve each hypothesis in turn with full statistical evidence. Section 4.7 presents the SHAP decomposition as an interpretability proof. Section 4.8 translates the AUC gains into financial impact terms. Section 4.9 addresses limitations honestly.

All results derive from five-fold stratified cross-validation. All preprocessing — median imputation and StandardScaler normalisation — was fit exclusively on training folds, guaranteeing zero forward-looking leakage into the held-out fold @mackinlay1997 @creswell2014.

== Model Ablation Results

